    "name": "School Inventory Management API",
    "description": "Postman collection aligned with the current backend routes and payloads.\n\nAuthentication note:\n- /auth/login returns the access token in JSON and sets the refresh token as an httpOnly cookie.\n- In Postman, keep the cookie jar enabled for /auth/refresh and /auth/logout to work without manually pasting a refresh token.\n- The refreshToken body field is optional fallback input when you already have the token value from another client.\n- /auth/forgot-password always returns a generic success message; when email delivery is enabled, copy the raw token from the reset link in the email and paste it into the passwordResetToken collection variable before calling /auth/reset-password.",
